![high](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/high-priority.svg)

Type mismatch: The `timelines` input is typed as `ReadonlyDomainElement<Timeline[]>` (a single element wrapping an array), but `timeline-frame.component.ts` passes `ReadonlyDomainElement<Timeline>[]` (an array of elements). This will cause a TypeScript compilation error. It should be typed as `ReadonlyDomainElement<Timeline>[]`.

```suggestion
  /** The list of resource timelines to display in the index. */
  timelines = input<ReadonlyDomainElement<Timeline>[]>([]);
```

