Throwing an error inside the WebGL render loop will halt the entire rendering pipeline and crash the application UI. It is safer to log the error to the console and return early, skipping rendering for this specific timeline.

```suggestion
    if (!layerStyleUBO) {
      console.error(
        'UBO for TimelineType ID ' + this.timeline.type.id + ' not found',
      );
      return;
    }
```

